  "strategy_guide_spot_martingale_page1_title" : "What is Spot Martingale?",
  "strategy_guide_spot_martingale_page2_title" : "Advantages of Spot Martingale",
  "strategy_guide_spot_martingale_page3_title" : "How to trade with Spot Martingale",
  "strategy_guide_spot_martingale_page4_title" : "How to terminate Spot Martingale",
  "strategy_guide_spot_martingale_label" : "Volatile Market/Profit from Reversal/Advanced",
  "strategy_guide_spot_martingale_page1_paragraph1" : "Spot Martingale is a medium and long term automatic trading bot that helps users to reduce their average cost. ",
  "strategy_guide_spot_martingale_page1_paragraph2" : "By setting parameters such as &quot;Price Deviation&quot;, &quot;Amount Multiplier&quot;, and &quot;TP Target Per Cycle&quot;, the bot increases the investment each time the price falls, continuously buying in batches to dilute the holding cost, and then sells all at once when the price rebounds, profiting from reversal.",
  "strategy_guide_spot_martingale_page2_paragraph1" : "If you believe that a certain cryptocurrency is worth holding, and you think it won't be in a one-way market for long, you can choose the Spot DCA bot.",
  "strategy_guide_spot_martingale_page2_paragraph2" : "1. High Win Rate: The bot can be consistently profitable in a medium- to long-term volatile market.\n2. Greater Capital Efficiency: The bot increases the amount whenever it buys in batches to dilute the holding cost, maximizing the capital efficiency.\n3. Manageable Risk: The bot does not use leverage. It buys coins at a user-set Price Deviation with a Max DCA Orders limit to keep the risk manageable.",
  "strategy_guide_spot_martingale_page3_paragraph1" : "There are three methods:",
  "strategy_guide_spot_martingale_page3_paragraph2" : "1. Follow a bot provider/Copy a backtesting bot: You can filter out top performers or backtesting bots in the Recommended section and follow a provider or copy a bot to trade.\n2. Choose a bot that matches your trading style: We offer three types of backtesting bot, which are HODL, High-Risk Arbitrage, and Low-Risk Arbitrage. You can choose one to copy according to your trading style and risk appetite.\n3. Customize your own bot: You can choose coins as you want, and start your own bot by setting the bot's parameters.\nTips: Mainstream tokens are recommended when using spot martingale bot. As they are more likely to rebound from a fall and thus to avoid huge drawdown.",
  "strategy_guide_spot_martingale_page4_paragraph1" : "You can terminate Spot Martingale at any time. Please note:",
  "strategy_guide_spot_martingale_page4_paragraph2" : "1. Spot Martingale should be terminated timely when a coin has been in a one-sided market.\n2. When the bot ends, the remaining coin will be transferred to your Spot Account. You can then decide whether to sell coin in the spot market or not.\n3. Spot Martingale is used for medium to long-term volatile markets, so in the short term there may be floating losses as the price has not reversed yet. Please monitor the market trend to invest with caution.",
  "strategy_tp_per_cycle_error_tip" : "TP Target Per Cycle should be no less than {s}",
